Package: statz
Title: Statistical Functions with Rust Engines
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Zachary", "Daulat", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "zdaulat@gmail.com")
Description: Pedagogical implentation of statistical and causal inference 
    functions and tools using Rust via extendr. Strictly pedagogical
    implementations cover descriptive statistics, probability distributions, 
    regressions, and spatial analysis methods. Includes a variation of 
    Distributional Synthetic Controls (DiSC) via 2-Wasserstein distance
    minimization with L2 regularization for highly collinear donor pools.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
